<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1220,1643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,422,1220,1246]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Taxonomical remarks.</emphasis>
The examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[713,761,1221,1247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">type</typeStatus>
specimens revealed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sedivy" authorityYear="1965" box="[1055,1245,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[1055,1245,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(described from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,254,1256,1282]" name="Romania" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Romania</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dbar" authorityYear="1985" box="[318,583,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiterebra">
<emphasis box="[318,583,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa longiterebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(described from Crimea) are undoubtedly conspecific, therefore 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dbar" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiterebra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa longiterebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sedivy" authorityYear="1965" box="[806,992,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[806,992,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the latest revision of the Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holmgren" box="[151,269,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,269,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dbar, R. S." box="[376,510,1328,1354]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="802 - 812" refId="ref5881" refString="Dbar, R. S. (1984) Review of the Palaearctic species of the genus Cymodusa Holmgren (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae). I. Entomologicheskoye Obozreniye, 63, 802 - 812. (in Russian)" type="journal article" year="1984">Dbar (1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dbar, R. S." box="[524,581,1328,1355]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="588 - 600" refId="ref5921" refString="Dbar, R. S. (1985) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Cymodusa Holmgren (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae). II. Entomologicheskoye Obozreniye, 64, 588 - 600. (in Russian)" type="journal article" year="1985">1985</bibRefCitation>
) did not mention 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sedivy" authorityYear="1965" box="[790,979,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[790,979,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at all; most probably he was not aware of 
<bibRefCitation author="Sedivy, J." box="[182,347,1364,1392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="163 - 176" refId="ref6724" refString="Sedivy, J. (1965) Neue und interessante Ichneumoniden aus Rumanien. Sbornik Faunistickych Praci Entomologickeho Oddeleni Narodniho Musea v Praze, 10, 163 - 176." type="journal article" year="1965">Šedivý (1965)</bibRefCitation>
’s paper, as the species description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dbar" authorityYear="1985" box="[770,1035,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiterebra">
<emphasis box="[770,1035,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa longiterebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits entirely with that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sedivy" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="272" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1220,1643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1436,1462]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sedivy" authorityYear="1965" box="[328,514,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[328,514,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguishable from the other Palaearctic species of the “australis” group (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Dbar, R. S." box="[229,377,1472,1499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="588 - 600" refId="ref5921" refString="Dbar, R. S. (1985) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Cymodusa Holmgren (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae). II. Entomologicheskoye Obozreniye, 64, 588 - 600. (in Russian)" type="journal article" year="1985">Dbar (1985))</bibRefCitation>
, it is the only species with ovipositor sheath longer (1.15–1.25×) than hind tibia, and the deeply impressed, very strongly trans-striated area petiolaris is also characteristic. Propodeal carination as in 
<figureCitation box="[1283,1351,1508,1534]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,395,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-103@3.[151,1436,381,1853]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Morphological details of Cymodusa species. 1–5, Cymodusa irata sp. nov.; 1, habitus (holotype); 2, head, female; 3, areolet; 4, propodeum; 5, head, male; 6, Cymodusa nigra Šedivý, propodeum; 7–8, Cymodusa australis (Smits van Burgst), propodeum, variations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810176/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
. Tegula dark, metasoma black, hind femur reddish, hind tibia reddish, basally with a pale spot, subbasally and apically slightly darkened. Males can also be reliably identified by characters of propodeum and colouration. Body length ca. 
<quantity box="[190,286,1616,1643]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
